        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>OFFICE OF<lb/>
            &#34;The Jewish Messenger&#44;&#34;<lb/>
            243 BROADWAY.<lb/>
            Rev. S. M. ISAACS &#38; SONS&#44; Editors and Proprietors.<lb/>
            New York&#44; Jan. 7 1869.<lb/>
            Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
            Rev &#38; Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>In opening the<lb/> new volume of our Journal&#44;<lb/> we have determined to make<lb/> it exceed its predecessors in<lb/> interest&#44; and to cause it to be<lb/> in reality what we have ever<lb/> desired to make it&#8212;the<lb/> leading and best of the<lb/> Jewish papers.<lb/></p>
            <p>With this view&#44; we have<lb/> decided to secure the best<lb/> talent that can be found<lb/> in Jewish circles&#44; as con&#45;<lb/>tributors and for this pur&#45;<lb/>pose we are ready to<lb/> enter into arrangements<lb/> with all who may desire<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to enter the field of Jewish<lb/> literature.<lb/></p>
            <p>Among these we are espec<lb/>ially desirous of securing<lb/> your valuable assistance<lb/>&#45;&#45;while sincerely thanking<lb/> you for the many times that<lb/> you have written for our<lb/> pages.<lb/></p>
            <p>Can you not write for us<lb/> more regularly either on<lb/> general subjects or on one or<lb/> two continuous themes&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>At present we can offer<lb/> these terms&#8212;with the expec&#45;<lb/>tation of bettering them in a<lb/> few months&#44; if we find our<lb/> circulation materially in&#45;<lb/>creasing&#8212;five dollars per<lb/> column as an average note.<lb/></p>
            <p>You might state in your<lb/> reply what subjects you would<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>wish to treat about&#44; and<lb/> from your list we might select<lb/> such as we deem suitable<lb/>
            There is a good field in the<lb/> Rabbis&#44; Spanish and Italian<lb/> sages.<lb/>
            But as to this&#44; we would pre&#45;<lb/>fer to hear your opinion.<lb/>
            Trusting this proposition<lb/> will be received favora&#45;<lb/>bly&#44; and assuring you of<lb/> our personal esteem<lb/></p>
            <p>We are<lb/>
            Yours Truly<lb/>
            S M Isaacs &#38; Sons<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>OFFICE OF<lb/>
            The Jewish Messenger&#44;<lb/>
            243 Broadway&#44;<lb/>
            NEW YORK.<lb/>
            REV. S. M. ISAACS &#38; SONS&#44;<lb/>
            EDITORS AND PROPRIETORS.<lb/>
            Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/>
            Philadelphia<lb/>
            Penn<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
